properties.sfomuseum:description: b-c. handwritten letter from Jimmy (James) McKinley to Mary McKinley, his mother; stationery from the Navy Young Men’s Christian Association in Pearl Harbor; describes his journey aboard a naval ship and his first impressions of Oahu.d. military leave request form; Base Force, United States Fleet; completed by James Ross McKinley on August 3, 1938, requesting one week’s leave; request denied.
